1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:07,132
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:16,641 --> 00:00:18,226
[Nestor] <i>I saw Saint Anthony last night.</i>

3
00:00:18,309 --> 00:00:20,437
<i>He was drifting</i>
<i>away from the church, Father.</i>

4
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,938
- [Emerson] "Shzzug."
- [congregation gasps]

5
00:00:22,021 --> 00:00:23,398
Could that have been a car door?

6
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:24,441
Maybe it was!

7
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:27,694
[Atoy] <i>Miss, your CCTV captures</i>
<i>everyone who passes by, right?</i>

8
00:00:27,777 --> 00:00:29,571
<i>I'm trying to track a plate number.</i>

9
00:00:29,654 --> 00:00:32,615
DPR Tracking Services.

10
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:33,742
[Merly] <i>Sir, that was delivered to me.</i>

11
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:35,201
<i>Twenty-nine pieces.</i>

12
00:00:35,285 --> 00:00:37,704
[Red] <i>You shouldn't be accepting</i>
<i>deliveries, especially</i>

13
00:00:37,787 --> 00:00:39,205
<i>when you don't know who they're from.</i>

14
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:40,874
[Atoy] <i>Ivory fragments.</i>

15
00:00:40,957 --> 00:00:42,417
Who are you? Are you a cop?

16
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,335
No, I'm not.

17
00:00:44,919 --> 00:00:45,837
[Red] <i>Don't you ever come back!</i>

18
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:49,048
[Atoy] <i>Mate, get the police</i>
<i>down here to the port.</i>

19
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:50,550
<i>DPR Shipping.</i>

20
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,969
<i>That's the name of the container</i>
<i>that needs to be stopped. Got it?</i>

21
00:00:53,052 --> 00:00:55,263
PREVIOUSLY

22
00:00:55,346 --> 00:00:58,224
Hello. Finally, we meet.

23
00:00:58,808 --> 00:00:59,768
Why is this open?

24
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:03,521
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

25
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:05,523
[crane whirring]

26
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:06,441
‪[grunting and groaning]

27
00:01:07,609 --> 00:01:12,155
- [tense dramatic music]
- [Atoy groans]

28
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:13,615
[worker] <i>Security, security.</i>

29
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:15,658
<i>There's someone hanging</i>
<i>on the DPR container.</i>

30
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:19,871
[gun firing]

31
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:24,751
[brazen music continues]

32
00:01:25,585 --> 00:01:29,506
[gun firing]

33
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:40,475
[grunts]

34
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,322
[gun fires]

35
00:02:04,874 --> 00:02:06,668
- [gun firing]
- [bullets plinking]

36
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:09,379
- [worker 1] Hey!
- [dramatic bang]

37
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:10,338
You're not getting away this time.

38
00:02:10,421 --> 00:02:11,381
[worker 2] Who are you?!

39
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:13,591
Why are you raiding our container, huh?!

40
00:02:13,675 --> 00:02:14,759
Are you a cop?

41
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:15,802
[worker 1] Why won't you answer us?

42
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,262
Who sent you?

43
00:02:17,345 --> 00:02:24,060
[inquisitive music playing]

44
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:26,020
[worker 1] Who sent you here?

45
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:31,234
[crane whirring]

46
00:02:31,317 --> 00:02:32,402
God?

47
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:33,903
What nonsense is this?

48
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:35,613
[worker 1] You've lost it!

49
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:37,198
- [music intensifies]
- [worker screams]

50
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:38,825
[whacks]

51
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:45,623
[brazen music playing, concludes]

52
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,794
I was diagnosed with a brain tumor.

53
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:51,754
Malignant.

54
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,591
I never went back to the doctor.

55
00:02:54,674 --> 00:02:57,886
[glum music playing]

56
00:02:57,969 --> 00:02:59,262
Sometimes…

57
00:03:00,638 --> 00:03:02,265
my vision blurs,

58
00:03:02,807 --> 00:03:04,309
and I lose my temper so easily.

59
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:11,399
Why did you keep this to yourself?

60
00:03:11,482 --> 00:03:12,442
‪[sniffles]

61
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:15,945
For what?

62
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,324
So you can force me to go
through treatment again

63
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:22,201
for a disease that's already
going to kill me?

64
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:26,372
But you have to keep living
for your son. [sobs]

65
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:30,585
There's no more hope left for me.

66
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:32,337
‪[Cita sobbing]

67
00:03:32,420 --> 00:03:35,089
The only thing on my mind now is Atoy.

68
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:38,635
I won't stop him from leaving anymore.

69
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:43,181
But when I'm gone,

70
00:03:44,515 --> 00:03:46,684
I want him to have a family
he can come home to.

71
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:48,770
[Cita sobbing]

72
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:51,147
That's why you need to stay
on good terms with Atoy.

73
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:58,446
This is my karma, Cita.

74
00:03:59,572 --> 00:04:02,825
My punishment form God for the sins
I committed against my family.

75
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:07,038
[sobbing]

76
00:04:07,121 --> 00:04:11,084
[glum music continues]

77
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:21,594
- [water sloshing]
- [gasping]

78
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:25,974
[stirring music playing]

79
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,444
Let's face this together.

80
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,905
I'll help you out. Come on.

81
00:04:45,076 --> 00:04:48,413
[suave music playing]

82
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:50,123
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

83
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:36,627
[sobbing]

84
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:40,006
[somber music playing]

85
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:41,549
Cita, stop crying now.

86
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:43,801
I'm not dead yet.

87
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,055
You're unbelievable.

88
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:49,474
I can't believe you're joking
at a time like this.

89
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:53,144
But Atoy needs to know.

90
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:56,105
Don't tell him.

91
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:58,232
Don't you ever tell him.

92
00:05:58,316 --> 00:06:02,028
- Still, he has the right to know--
- I don't want him to pity me!

93
00:06:02,111 --> 00:06:06,032
- [somber music playing]
- [scoffs]

94
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:10,369
I don't want you
to feel sorry for me either.

95
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:14,582
All I want from you is one thing.

96
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:16,751
That when I'm gone,

97
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:19,045
you'll look after my son.

98
00:06:19,128 --> 00:06:20,671
[Cita moans pitifully]

99
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:21,631
Promise me?

100
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:23,841
‪[whimpers]

101
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:28,096
Promise me?

102
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:35,103
[somber music continues]

103
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:46,405
[tense music playing]

104
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:49,742
Saint Anthony?

105
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:52,870
[Atoy] It's not too late to change.

106
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:56,249
[Atoy imitating an old man]
You can still turn your life around.

107
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,251
My God…

108
00:06:59,627 --> 00:07:01,796
Saint Anthony is speaking to me.

109
00:07:03,714 --> 00:07:06,008
I promise I'll change!

110
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:09,137
[sobbing]

111
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:13,808
[tense music turns whimsical]

112
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:28,239
[whimsical music continues]

113
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:29,449
Atoy?

114
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:33,035
What's going on with the shipping?
I'm confused.

115
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:36,122
Get over here. Report to me directly.

116
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:39,208
And if you get caught alive,
I'll kill you myself.

117
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:44,755
- [unsettling music playing]
- [disconnect beep]

118
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:46,048
Red.

119
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:47,258
[Red] Dad.

120
00:07:47,341 --> 00:07:50,470
How's the delivery for Mr. Agustin?

121
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:51,721
[rapid beeping]

122
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:54,348
The shipment's on its way tonight, right?

123
00:07:54,765 --> 00:07:59,103
Uh… Yes, there was a small problem
with the paperwork,

124
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:00,480
but it's all sorted now.

125
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:01,522
[in English] Is that all?

126
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:02,648
Yes.

127
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:08,196
Um, by the way,
Martina made dinner. Let's eat.

128
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:10,823
[in English] Hmm… I'm not feeling it.

129
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:12,867
I'll stay with your sister instead.

130
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:15,161
Her vitals are improving.

131
00:08:16,412 --> 00:08:18,748
Audrey won't be waking up tonight, Dad.

132
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:20,166
Come on, let's eat first.

133
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:23,294
[in English] You'll never know.

134
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:28,132
I want my face to be the first one…

135
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:31,511
[stirring dramatic music playing]

136
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:33,429
…my prodigal daughter sees.

137
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:46,943
[tense dramatic music playing]

138
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:51,113
The entire batch
has been intercepted, all the ivory?

139
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,448
[in English] Yes, Dad.

140
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,535
Don't worry. I'm already on it.

141
00:08:57,662 --> 00:09:01,207
[in English] No. You told me
everything's going well.

142
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,460
Your team has failed again!

143
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:08,256
And you! You are the same damn people

144
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:11,509
who failed bringing Audrey back.

145
00:09:11,592 --> 00:09:13,886
That is why she is still in a coma
to this day!

146
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:17,932
[tense music playing]

147
00:09:18,015 --> 00:09:20,059
Who are you people?! Help me!

148
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:23,980
[muffled screams]

149
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:25,147
[grunting and groaning]

150
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:26,607
- [goon groans]
- [Elaine gasps, groans]

151
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:28,067
- [goon grunts]
- [Elaine gasps]

152
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:36,826
[goon] Boss, I think you might
have killed Ma'am Audrey.

153
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:38,494
She's still alive! Get the house in order.

154
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:40,246
Gather everything properly.

155
00:09:40,329 --> 00:09:42,081
Make sure there's no sign of foul play.

156
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:45,334
Boss, it's fake.

157
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:48,796
[clinks]

158
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,049
[in English] I'm sorry, Dad.

159
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:54,760
[in English] Always a disappointment.

160
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:56,721
[sinister music playing]

161
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:58,431
This is all that meddler's doing.

162
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:00,808
Nothing like this
has ever happened before.

163
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:03,519
We even lost a few of our men
in the chase.

164
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:07,106
That's right, Sir Dmitri.
He completely ruined all our plans.

165
00:10:07,189 --> 00:10:09,942
The thing is,
no one saw the meddler's face

166
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:11,277
because he was too fast and too skilled.

167
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,612
Just let it go.

168
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:15,698
[in English] I'm done with all of this.

169
00:10:16,407 --> 00:10:17,533
[in English] No, Dad.

170
00:10:18,326 --> 00:10:19,785
I'll look for him.

171
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,663
[in English] No one crosses a Regalia.

172
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:34,759
[inquisitive music playing]

173
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:46,562
[Siony] Father, we'll begin the vigil
early tomorrow

174
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:49,690
in an effort to bring back
Saint Anthony of Padua.

175
00:10:50,232 --> 00:10:53,152
[Peping] I appreciate your devotion
to our patron.

176
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:57,657
[Siony] I hope we find him
before the fiesta.

177
00:10:57,740 --> 00:11:02,036
It's extremely heartbreaking
to see it empty…

178
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:07,166
- [gasps and chuckles]
- [sentimental music playing]

179
00:11:07,249 --> 00:11:08,125
Father…

180
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:10,711
- How is it already here?!
- [ladies gasp]

181
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:11,796
[all gasp]

182
00:11:11,879 --> 00:11:14,340
Father, is it true what we are seeing?

183
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:16,967
- Is this the real statue, Father?
- [ladies mutter]

184
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,594
- It wasn't even here earlier.
- [ladies gasping]

185
00:11:18,677 --> 00:11:20,388
We were just talking
over there a moment ago.

186
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:21,347
[ladies murmuring]

187
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:22,556
[woman] Thank God.

188
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:25,059
My God, thank you so much.

189
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:28,396
[Peping] Atoy!

190
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:31,107
Just a moment.

191
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:36,362
Did you see who brought the saint back?

192
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:40,408
It's back?

193
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:44,036
Oh, wow, it really is.

194
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:47,706
Father, he wouldn't have
any way of knowing.

195
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,500
He just got here.

196
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:55,047
[women murmuring]

197
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:59,927
[Siony chuckles] Miracles really do exist,
my, my, my…

198
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:05,433
[sentimental music continues]

199
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:07,768
[women buzzing]

200
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:09,186
[Peping] From now on, make sure
you keep a close watch on it, okay?

201
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,563
[woman] Yes, Father.

202
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:16,402
[sentimental music continues]

203
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:20,072
Miss Cita!

204
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:22,950
Miss Cita!

205
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:26,412
What are you doing here?
Why aren't you asleep yet?

206
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:28,873
It's really late. Where have you been?

207
00:12:28,956 --> 00:12:30,666
Ah… Well…

208
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:31,917
I just had a few things to take care of.

209
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:33,669
And I still have somewhere to go.

210
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:35,421
So…

211
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:37,965
Your father has been waiting
for you to come home.

212
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:41,260
[sentimental music playing]

213
00:12:41,343 --> 00:12:44,638
Come on. We both know that isn't true.

214
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:45,806
He has no reason to wait for me.

215
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:48,851
And even if he does, he shouldn't bother.

216
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:52,021
He shouldn't wait for me anymore,
because I'm leaving for good.

217
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:53,105
Atoy, please.

218
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:56,400
You can't leave him.

219
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:58,861
He needs you.

220
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:03,407
Well… [chuckles]

221
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:07,661
He gets so unbelievably mad at me
when I'm only touching his things,

222
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:09,538
like he already thinks
I'm trying to mess with them.

223
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:12,583
Really. You know…

224
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:17,338
I really don't think we're meant
to live under the same roof anymore.

225
00:13:18,255 --> 00:13:21,258
[in English] We've simply grown apart.

226
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:24,136
Stop being so hardheaded.

227
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:25,763
You stay here.

228
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:28,891
Fix your relationship with your dad,

229
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:33,395
so you can stop telling yourself
"grown apart".

230
00:13:36,148 --> 00:13:37,107
Come on.

231
00:13:39,109 --> 00:13:40,819
You know it's easier said than done.

232
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:42,613
Why are you pushing this so hard?

233
00:13:42,696 --> 00:13:44,073
You know he's not in his right mind.

234
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:47,451
You need to make things right
before it's too late!

235
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:51,372
[sobbing]

236
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:58,587
Miss Cita… Are you all right?

237
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:00,214
What's wrong?

238
00:14:05,594 --> 00:14:07,721
Your dad has cancer.

239
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:11,392
You cannot leave him.

240
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:16,397
[dramatic music playing]

241
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:31,579
[pensive music playing]

242
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,664
[Cita sobbing]

243
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:34,790
Hold on…

244
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:38,335
What… What are you talking about?

245
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:40,129
Come on. Stop messing with me.

246
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:41,672
Your acting skills
are definitely improving.

247
00:14:41,755 --> 00:14:44,508
You're just saying that
so I won't leave, right?

248
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:48,929
[sobbing] I wish that were true!
I wish I were lying!

249
00:14:50,014 --> 00:14:51,307
But I'm not, Atoy…

250
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:54,935
Your dad really has a brain tumor.

251
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:59,398
[sobbing]

252
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:03,485
Maybe it's his trick again?

253
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:04,945
I can't believe
he would use this trick again.

254
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:06,655
- I need to have a word with him.
- Atoy, no!

255
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:08,032
Atoy, stop!

256
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:16,999
Is it true?

257
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:19,960
What do you mean?

258
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:21,629
That you have cancer.

259
00:15:23,797 --> 00:15:24,965
Atoy…

260
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,593
Miss Cita told me.

261
00:15:28,552 --> 00:15:29,678
You told him?

262
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:31,889
I'm sorry, Delfin.

263
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,474
Why did I trust you!?

264
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:38,228
[dramatic music playing]

265
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:39,480
So it's true.

266
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:41,273
Um…

267
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:45,402
Well, what did the doctor say?

268
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:46,695
Um…

269
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:48,781
What treatment are you getting?

270
00:15:48,864 --> 00:15:49,865
None.

271
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:51,200
That won't be necessary anymore.

272
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:53,452
None?

273
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,830
What are you talking about?
Are you in remission already?

274
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:59,875
No! Treatment won't be necessary anymore.

275
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:01,126
I've stopped going for check-ups!

276
00:16:02,336 --> 00:16:03,963
[Atoy] Hold on. But w-why?!

277
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,714
Why aren't you getting treatment?

278
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,508
You need to see a doctor!

279
00:16:07,591 --> 00:16:09,593
Dad, this is serious.

280
00:16:09,677 --> 00:16:11,720
You really need
to get checked by a doctor, Dad.

281
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,597
Just think about it… [stammers]

282
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:15,057
You're getting older. [stammers]

283
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,684
It's hopeless!

284
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:18,811
I'm about to die anyway!

285
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:23,148
[whimpering]

286
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:27,111
[dramatic music continues]

287
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:29,446
[in English] Stage 4.

288
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:33,325
[in English] Poor prognosis.

289
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:42,501
Treatment and check-ups
won't make any difference at this point.

290
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:46,547
[dramatic music continues]

291
00:17:07,651 --> 00:17:10,237
‪[music concludes]

292
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:18,370
[in English] I trust you and your contact
will take care of everything.

293
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:21,707
[life monitoring machine beeping]

294
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:24,293
[in English] Good. Thank you.

295
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,881
I can't believe I'm still
cleaning up your mess.

296
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:33,552
[unsettling music playing]

297
00:17:33,635 --> 00:17:35,846
- [nurse, in English] Excuse me, sir.
- [in English] Yes?

298
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:38,474
It looks like Ma'am Audrey
has a bit of swelling.

299
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:40,350
[in English] Meaning?

300
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:42,394
[in English] It could be an infection
or something else.

301
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:44,772
It's best to have her checked
by the doctor immediately,

302
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:47,483
so we can also request
for any necessary tests.

303
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:51,153
[unsettling music continues]

304
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:53,238
‪[music concludes]

305
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:59,912
SIR DELFIN'S
TAILORING SHOP

306
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:17,679
You just found out?

307
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:25,354
I noticed he was struggling.

308
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:27,231
I thought it was something minor.

309
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:31,026
I had no idea it was this serious.

310
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:37,825
I just don't get Delfin.

311
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:42,412
Why didn't he get treatment
when he has the means?

312
00:18:44,373 --> 00:18:47,167
Also, he should have told me sooner.

313
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:49,837
I mean, we're always together.

314
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,713
Why did he have to keep it a secret?

315
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:58,679
I don't even know
why I'm the one panicking.

316
00:18:58,762 --> 00:18:59,680
You should be the one worrying.

317
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,600
Anyway, how are you?

318
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:09,940
I honestly don't know.

319
00:19:10,023 --> 00:19:12,151
[sentimental music playing]

320
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:13,318
Atoy…

321
00:19:15,654 --> 00:19:18,574
You can get mad at me all you want.

322
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:23,495
But I hope you and your dad
can make things right.

323
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:28,542
After all, everyone makes mistakes
without meaning to.

324
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:30,460
But if…

325
00:19:31,295 --> 00:19:33,297
If you can humble yourself,

326
00:19:36,216 --> 00:19:39,052
do it now, while there's still time,

327
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:42,598
while there's still a chance.

328
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:51,231
Before… it's too late.

329
00:19:55,694 --> 00:20:02,367
[sobbing]

330
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,293
Cita! What is it?

331
00:20:11,376 --> 00:20:13,629
It's late at night,
and you're still outside.

332
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:15,839
- I'm heading home. Come on.
- Let's go. It's time to sleep.

333
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:26,683
[sentimental music playing]

334
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:33,523
Dad, when I grow up,
I want to build a shop like this.

335
00:20:33,607 --> 00:20:37,611
Why would you still want one?
I'll be giving all of this to you anyway.

336
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:39,571
You're giving me this shop?

337
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:41,573
Of course!

338
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:43,825
You know, Atoy…

339
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:45,827
Um…

340
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:50,332
The only thing I can leave you

341
00:20:50,415 --> 00:20:53,085
is everything I know
about sewing and alterations.

342
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:57,673
Also, it's best if you start preparing.

343
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:00,259
Keep our business running
once I'm gone, okay?

344
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,052
[sniffling]

345
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,556
[whimpering] Dad… Dad…

346
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,809
Hey, why-w-why are you…
Why are you crying?

347
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:11,603
Dad, I don't want you to die!

348
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:15,691
Atoy, my son…

349
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:17,859
Don't worry. It won't happen right away.

350
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:21,405
- It's okay. Don't cry, please.
- [sobs]

351
00:21:21,488 --> 00:21:23,532
I'm not going anywhere, all right?

352
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:25,617
We still have a long way to go.

353
00:21:25,701 --> 00:21:27,619
You love me very much, don't you?

354
00:21:28,203 --> 00:21:31,081
Yes, I love you so much.

355
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:32,624
You know what?

356
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,418
[sobbing]

357
00:21:34,501 --> 00:21:36,712
I love my Atoy just as much.

358
00:21:37,296 --> 00:21:39,298
Settle down now. Don't cry.

359
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:41,758
I'm not going anywhere.

360
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:45,470
Hey, why is he crying?

361
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:47,306
- Atoy, why are you crying?
- Mom…

362
00:21:47,889 --> 00:21:50,100
Let's hug him so he feels better.

363
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:52,769
Come on. Don't cry!

364
00:21:52,853 --> 00:21:53,812
Why are you crying? [smooches]

365
00:21:53,895 --> 00:21:55,689
I love you so much.

366
00:21:55,772 --> 00:21:57,774
We love you just as much.

367
00:21:57,858 --> 00:21:59,026
We love you.

368
00:22:00,068 --> 00:22:02,487
[Julie] <i>Hmm!</i> [chuckles]

369
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:09,369
[intense music playing]

370
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:17,502
- Mom, can I go now?
- [Cita] Huh?

371
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:21,256
I will play basketball with Billy, please?

372
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:24,593
Wow, impressive.

373
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:25,927
I didn't know Karla
liked playing basketball.

374
00:22:26,011 --> 00:22:27,637
Maybe we can do a one-on-one sometime.

375
00:22:28,221 --> 00:22:29,347
- Huh?
- Sure thing.

376
00:22:32,517 --> 00:22:34,394
- [Karla] Good morning!
- [Cita exclaims]

377
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:35,687
[in English] Good morning.

378
00:22:35,771 --> 00:22:36,855
[in English] Good morning!

379
00:22:36,938 --> 00:22:38,065
Your coffee's ready.

380
00:22:38,648 --> 00:22:39,983
Thank you, Cita.

381
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:44,446
Atoy made that for you.

382
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,743
I'm not the only person you should thank.
You should be thanking Atoy too.

383
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:56,833
Thank you, son.

384
00:23:03,632 --> 00:23:06,676
[reporter] <i>In other news,</i>
<i>our apologies to those who are eating.</i>

385
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,638
<i>A man was killed</i>
<i>in the early hours of the morning</i>

386
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:13,809
<i>after being struck</i>
<i>by a container van at the port area.</i>

387
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:16,937
<i>The victim has been identified</i>
<i>as Damian Veloso,</i>

388
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:20,148
<i>an employee of DPR Tracking Services.</i>

389
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:21,650
<i>Because of this incident,</i>

390
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:25,570
<i>the police also discovered</i>
<i>that the container van was loaded</i>

391
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:28,115
<i>with illegally acquired ivory.</i>

392
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:29,908
<i>Authorities have launched</i>
<i>a full-scale investigation into</i>

393
00:23:29,991 --> 00:23:33,662
- <i>the company involved…</i>
- Isn't that the San Antonio statue lead,

394
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:34,788
the one tied to the ivory?

395
00:23:34,871 --> 00:23:36,748
[woman] Sir Delfin!

396
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:39,000
The patron reportedly
came back last night!

397
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:40,752
[woman] Let's go check it out. Come on!

398
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:41,878
- Come on. Let's go!
- [shrieks]

399
00:23:46,007 --> 00:23:51,346
[unsettling music playing]

400
00:23:58,103 --> 00:23:59,020
[clears throat]

401
00:24:18,915 --> 00:24:22,711
[crowd buzzing]

402
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:25,422
Wow, the patron has returned at last.

403
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:27,966
But how? Who brought him here?

404
00:24:28,049 --> 00:24:29,342
[Peping] We don't know either.

405
00:24:29,426 --> 00:24:32,095
[Nestor] It could have been Atoy!

406
00:24:32,179 --> 00:24:33,638
That's right!

407
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:35,056
[indistinct murmuring]

408
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:36,057
Are you sure it was Atoy who returned it?

409
00:24:36,141 --> 00:24:38,810
Oh, I had a word
with the patron last night.

410
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:42,147
He and Atoy were together.

411
00:24:43,231 --> 00:24:44,524
They're this close.

412
00:24:44,608 --> 00:24:46,610
[crowd buzzing]

413
00:24:46,693 --> 00:24:48,486
Oh, Nestor, you're drunk again.

414
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:49,738
[Emerson] Nestor,
you've been drinking again.

415
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:51,239
You should have invited us
to drink with you.

416
00:24:51,323 --> 00:24:54,618
- Are we in the right church? Right here?
- They're close!

417
00:24:54,701 --> 00:24:56,411
[Emerson] Goodness!

418
00:24:57,162 --> 00:25:00,624
Are you sure it was Atoy who returned it?

419
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:02,876
Hey, it wasn't him!

420
00:25:03,376 --> 00:25:06,630
The patron got there before him
last night!

421
00:25:07,881 --> 00:25:10,050
Wasn't he in the military?

422
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:12,469
Do they even train them
for stuff like this in the military?

423
00:25:12,552 --> 00:25:13,637
[man] Impressive!

424
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:14,930
He's a saint and a soldier
at the same time!

425
00:25:15,555 --> 00:25:16,640
- [man 1] Dimwit!
- [man 2 gasps]

426
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:18,808
It's called Search and…

427
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:19,976
Search…

428
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:21,978
- Search and Found?
- Search and Rescue?

429
00:25:22,062 --> 00:25:25,357
Search and Rescue? Really now?

430
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:27,525
It's called Search and Retrieval.

431
00:25:28,151 --> 00:25:29,027
[Siony] Come on.

432
00:25:29,110 --> 00:25:34,115
Atoy's mom conceived him in honor
of Saint Anthony of Padua, remember?

433
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:35,909
[Nestor stammers] That's it!

434
00:25:35,992 --> 00:25:39,621
Now it makes sense why the patron
went straight to Atoy!

435
00:25:39,704 --> 00:25:40,664
Exactly!

436
00:25:41,831 --> 00:25:44,334
[crowd buzzing]

437
00:25:44,417 --> 00:25:45,877
- Look, it's Atoy.
- Oh, Atoy's here.

438
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:47,128
Atoy!

439
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:48,588
[unsettling music]

440
00:25:48,672 --> 00:25:50,882
Thank you so much
for returning the patron.

441
00:25:50,966 --> 00:25:53,718
You tell them just how tight
you and the patron are.

442
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:54,844
Go ahead, tell them!

443
00:25:54,928 --> 00:25:56,513
- [man] Tell us! Tell us, Atoy!
- Tell us!

444
00:25:56,596 --> 00:25:58,682
Huh? What are you talking about?
That's not even true.

445
00:25:59,266 --> 00:26:00,141
[Emerson] I told you so.

446
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:02,185
If it wasn't Atoy
who brought it back here…

447
00:26:03,728 --> 00:26:04,938
- Then who did?
- [Siony] Who?

448
00:26:06,439 --> 00:26:09,276
He did. Go tell them, Atoy!

449
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:11,194
Tell them the truth!

450
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:13,905
[Siony] Just a moment. Hear me out.

451
00:26:13,989 --> 00:26:15,991
I bet it was Nestor who did it.

452
00:26:16,074 --> 00:26:17,450
Now that I think about it,

453
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:20,537
you were the only one here last night
when the patron was returned.

454
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:23,039
It's high time you came clean!

455
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:26,084
[Peping] Everyone, listen up!

456
00:26:26,167 --> 00:26:29,254
It no longer matters how it was returned.

457
00:26:29,838 --> 00:26:31,381
What matters is that it's back,

458
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:35,844
and you've also proven
that you can come together

459
00:26:35,927 --> 00:26:39,556
when there's a problem to solve.

460
00:26:40,557 --> 00:26:43,810
Perhaps the patron's return was a miracle,

461
00:26:44,311 --> 00:26:49,607
or maybe it was the kindness
of someone who truly sought it,

462
00:26:50,191 --> 00:26:51,484
or maybe…

463
00:26:52,402 --> 00:26:54,863
through your presence and unity,

464
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:58,491
you've kept your faith
in each other and in the Lord.

465
00:26:58,575 --> 00:27:01,578
Long live the people
of Barangay Tabang Lupa!

466
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:04,748
[crowd] Long live!

467
00:27:04,831 --> 00:27:06,041
[applauding]

468
00:27:06,124 --> 00:27:07,375
Are you sure it wasn't you?

469
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,920
I'm going to look for the statue now.

470
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:12,797
[curious music playing]

471
00:27:12,881 --> 00:27:14,716
Once it's done, let's forget each other.

472
00:27:16,926 --> 00:27:20,013
He shouldn't wait for me anymore,
because I'm leaving for good.

473
00:27:20,096 --> 00:27:21,973
[crowd applauding]

474
00:27:22,057 --> 00:27:25,101
All I can say is thank you
to whoever returned the patron.

475
00:27:25,185 --> 00:27:27,979
And as for the one who stole
San Antonio De Padua,

476
00:27:28,063 --> 00:27:29,856
karma's going on their way.

477
00:27:29,939 --> 00:27:30,857
[crowd buzzing]

478
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:32,192
‪[Cita groans]

479
00:27:32,275 --> 00:27:38,948
[brazen music continues]

480
00:27:41,201 --> 00:27:43,119
[electronic blipping]

481
00:27:43,203 --> 00:27:49,167
[intense music playing]

482
00:27:49,250 --> 00:27:52,670
He's got a lead on that fool
who meddled in our operations.

483
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:54,464
[Paldo] He used to be in the army, sir.

484
00:27:54,547 --> 00:27:56,257
He's the son of our tailor.

485
00:27:56,341 --> 00:27:59,594
- [car revving]
- [tires screeching]

486
00:27:59,677 --> 00:28:00,512
‪UP NEXT

487
00:28:00,595 --> 00:28:02,472
[crowd clamoring]

488
00:28:02,555 --> 00:28:03,932
[man] Let's help him!

489
00:28:04,015 --> 00:28:06,017
Sir, it looks like you
might have killed Atoy's father.

490
00:28:06,101 --> 00:28:07,477
Serves him right.

491
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:09,270
His life was the price
for his son's mistakes.

492
00:28:09,354 --> 00:28:12,899
If possible, give me all the details.
I'm going after that fool.

493
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:14,818
- I'm leaving everything to you.
- You can count on me, sir.

494
00:28:14,901 --> 00:28:16,486
No force can stop me…

495
00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:19,447
[both] From tracking it down.

496
00:28:24,411 --> 00:28:26,287
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
